.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINYEARMONTH.ERAYEAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.eraYear \-
Temporal.PlainYearMonth.prototype.eraYear
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]eraYear\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] instances returns a non\-negative
integer representing the year of this year\-month within the era, or
\f[CR]undefined\f[R] if the calendar does not use eras (e.g., ISO 8601).
The year index usually starts from 1 (more common) or 0, and years in an
era can decrease with time (e.g., Gregorian BCE).
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] together uniquely identify a year
in a calendar, in the same way that \f[CR]year\f[R] does.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]with()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainYearMonth\f[R] object with the desired new value.
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.eraYear\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using eraYear
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ym = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\(dq); \f[I]// ISO 8601 calendar\f[R]
console.log(ym.eraYear); \f[I]// undefined\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] ym2 = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=gregory]\(dq);
console.log(ym2.eraYear); \f[I]// 2021\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] ym3 = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq\-002021\-07\-01[u\-ca=gregory]\(dq);
console.log(ym3.eraYear); \f[I]// 2022; 0000 is used for the year 1 BC\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] ym4 = Temporal.PlainYearMonth.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=japanese]\(dq);
console.log(ym4.eraYear); \f[I]// 3\f[R]
.EE
